<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-03-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-03-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="643" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d643">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Wharton</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">von Holleben</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-03-10"><hi rend="italic">March 10,
                                1892</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to Mr. von Mumm’s note of the 3d
                            instant, relative to the action of your Government in authorizing the
                            acting imperial consul at Apia to select a person to act provisionally
                            as land commissioner until the arrival of the commissioner who is soon
                            to be appointed, I have the honor to inform you that this Government
                            accepts the temporary expedient in the expectation that the permanent
                            appointment of Mr. Eggert’s successor will be made as soon as
                            possible.</p>
                        <p>Accept, sir, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">William F. Wharton</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>